==English==
===Etymology===
Named after German [[physiologist]] [[w:Johannes Peter Müller|Johannes Peter Müller]] (1801-1858) who described the ducts in 1830.
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# A certain [[duct]] (of which there are two) in an [[embryo]] which in a [[female]] develop into the [[oviducts]], [[uterus]], [[cervix]] and upper [[vagina]].
